    <h3>The Team</h3>
    <p>Seed.coop is volunteer-powered, open source project, sponsored by the kind folks at <a href="https://colab.coop/">CoLab Coop</a> and steered by a committee of cooperative development experts with deep roots in economic and social justice movements.</p>

		<p>The technical development team has experience building a diverse array of IT systems from enterprise financial and commodities trading platforms for the likes of Suisse Bank and JP Morgan to building economic justice and community-advocacy platforms for the likes of Human Rights Campaign, NRDC Action Fund and the Unitarian Universalist Association.</p>

		<p>The cooperative development team hails from leading cooperative development organizations like the <a href="http://www.theselc.org/">Sustainable Economies Law Center</a>, the <a href="http://institute.coop/">Democracy at Work Institute</a>, <a href="http://www.lifteconomy.com/">LIFT Economy</a> and the <a href="https://usworker.coop/">US Federation of Worker Coops</a>.</p>

    <p>You can be a part of shaping the future of the Seed.Coop by pledging to become a member today.</p>

